1
00:00:21,856 --> 00:00:23,023
- It's over.
- It's over?

2
00:00:23,107 --> 00:00:24,233
What more do you want?

3
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:26,777
I want you to go to hell
the same way she did!

4
00:00:26,861 --> 00:00:29,363
You have no shame, showing your face here.

5
00:00:29,447 --> 00:00:30,906
Leave when you can...

6
00:00:30,990 --> 00:00:32,241
- Divino.
- You're alive!

7
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:34,118
Don't drag my family into this.

8
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:36,162
<i>I will never forgive you</i>
<i>for your betrayal.</i>

9
00:00:36,245 --> 00:00:38,831
- Ronnie, Raya isn't part of the plan.
- Raya ran away from home.

10
00:00:38,914 --> 00:00:40,332
Let's take Raya with us.

11
00:00:40,416 --> 00:00:42,168
Someone's coming! Come on! Get in!

12
00:00:42,251 --> 00:00:44,253
- <i>Where are Mama and Issay?</i>
- Why are you leaving us?

13
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:45,337
Go with them!

14
00:00:45,421 --> 00:00:47,840
- Split up!
- Let me go!

15
00:00:47,923 --> 00:00:49,133
Teo, show yourself!

16
00:00:49,216 --> 00:00:50,676
<i>Quick! Get him in the car!</i>

17
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:52,178
Let's get him to the hospital! Quick!

18
00:00:52,636 --> 00:00:54,054
Raya? Or should I say, Teo?

19
00:00:54,138 --> 00:00:55,931
Your son Ace took my sister.

20
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:57,349
You don't call the shots here, Teo.

21
00:00:57,433 --> 00:00:58,768
<i>You're a monster, Divino!</i>

22
00:00:58,851 --> 00:01:01,896
I'll give Issay back to you,
then you'll return Raya to me.

23
00:01:02,730 --> 00:01:06,066
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

24
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:36,639
<i>"We'll proceed. Tonight at 9 p.m."</i>

25
00:01:36,722 --> 00:01:38,516
<i>"At the vacant lot in Barangay Guan."</i>

26
00:01:39,975 --> 00:01:41,977
Raya, you know the plan.

27
00:01:43,521 --> 00:01:44,772
Yeah, sure.

28
00:01:50,611 --> 00:01:51,946
Come on.

29
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:55,950
Can we stop by a gas station
so I can use the restroom?

30
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:58,536
Gas station? No, come on.

31
00:02:00,246 --> 00:02:01,330
Jeez.

32
00:02:01,413 --> 00:02:02,540
Raya!

33
00:02:04,792 --> 00:02:06,961
Raya, come back here! Damn it!

34
00:02:07,753 --> 00:02:08,921
Raya!

35
00:02:09,004 --> 00:02:10,506
Cut it out!

36
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:12,299
Stop, Raya! Please!

37
00:02:13,801 --> 00:02:14,969
Raya, please stop!

38
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:17,137

Gem, I don't want any more trouble!

39
00:02:17,221 --> 00:02:18,931
I don't want you
to surrender yourself!

40
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:21,100
Yes, you were unfaithful to my brother,

41
00:02:21,183 --> 00:02:24,770
but you put up with
so much abuse from him.

42
00:02:26,105 --> 00:02:27,523
You can't go back.

43
00:02:27,982 --> 00:02:29,233
It's hell back there.

44
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:32,111

This has hurt too many people already.

45
00:02:32,194 --> 00:02:34,446
- My conscience can't take it anymore!

46
00:02:35,281 --> 00:02:36,615
Once I get home,

47
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:38,701
I will find a way to free Issay.

48
00:02:38,784 --> 00:02:39,952
Just please trust me.

49
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:41,579
Raya, no!

50
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:43,747
That's insane!

51
00:02:45,207 --> 00:02:47,877
This is the last time
you make decisions on your own.

52
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:53,132
If you want to make it up to Teo, show it!

53
00:02:53,215 --> 00:02:56,051
Don't forget what your father did.

54
00:02:57,845 --> 00:02:59,263
We need your cooperation.

55
00:03:01,974 --> 00:03:04,435
If you don't stick to the plan,
even if I go back there,

56
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:06,270
they still won't release Issay.

57
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:08,314
Is that what you want for Teo?

58
00:03:08,397 --> 00:03:10,149
For his family?

59
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,526
So please, Raya.

60
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:13,777
Come with me.

61
00:03:13,861 --> 00:03:14,987
Gem...

62
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,281
- Enough, okay?
Raya!

63
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:18,866
Raya!

64
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:20,659
- No!
Raya.

65
00:03:20,743 --> 00:03:22,369
- No.
Raya. Raya!

66
00:03:22,453 --> 00:03:24,496
- Raya!

67
00:03:24,580 --> 00:03:25,664


68
00:03:25,748 --> 00:03:28,500
- Gem! Gem!

69
00:03:28,584 --> 00:03:30,127
- Gem.

70
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,712
Are you okay?

71
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,464
- Are you okay, Gem?
Teo...

72
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:34,757


73
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,258
- Teo.
Gem.

74
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:39,762
-
Gem?

75
00:03:39,845 --> 00:03:41,931
- What's wrong?
The baby.

76
00:03:42,014 --> 00:03:44,683
- Huh?

77
00:03:53,859 --> 00:03:57,446


78
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,451
Doc.

79
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:04,328
Mr. Cruz, I'm so sorry.

80
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:06,538

We did everything we could, but...

81
00:04:07,206 --> 00:04:08,832
your wife lost the baby.

82
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,418
-
She's still weak.

83
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:14,380
She's still distraught,

84
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:16,715
so we need to monitor her for a few hours.

85
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,220
- Thank you, Doc.
Okay.

86
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:39,405


87
00:04:39,488 --> 00:04:40,572
Is it true?

88
00:04:41,699 --> 00:04:43,200
Is my baby gone?

89
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:45,703


90
00:04:47,246 --> 00:04:48,330
Sorry.

91
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:52,960
My baby...

92
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:57,297
That was my baby.

93
00:04:57,381 --> 00:04:58,716
My child.

94
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:03,846
- Shh, Gem.

95
00:05:03,929 --> 00:05:05,347
Why?

96
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:11,562


97
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:22,990


98
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,911


99
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,753


100
00:05:44,553 --> 00:05:45,971
Where are they?

101
00:05:46,055 --> 00:05:47,598

We checked the perimeter, sir.

102
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:48,849
They're not here.

103
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:51,185


104
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:53,937
-

105
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:59,526


106
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,236
Bullshit.

107
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:03,322
Come on!

108
00:06:25,928 --> 00:06:28,680


109
00:06:37,106 --> 00:06:39,691


110
00:06:41,193 --> 00:06:42,444
My child...

111
00:06:44,613 --> 00:06:46,115
I'm so sorry.

112
00:06:47,866 --> 00:06:50,119
Mama loves you so much.

113
00:06:50,202 --> 00:06:52,204
I didn't mean for this to happen.

114
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:02,422


115
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:09,680


116
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:51,889
Pearl.

117
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:53,724
Mike.

118
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:56,476
I've been waiting for you.

119
00:07:57,394 --> 00:08:00,230
The room upstairs is for the ladies.

120
00:08:00,314 --> 00:08:02,357
You boys can stay in the living room.

121
00:08:02,441 --> 00:08:03,775
There's food as well.

122
00:08:03,859 --> 00:08:06,028
If you need anything else,
just let me know.

123
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:07,571
I'll get it for you.

124
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:09,323
Thank you, Mike.

125
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:13,118
I didn't want to bother you,
but I had no choice.

126
00:08:13,202 --> 00:08:14,953
Sorry it took a while for me to respond.

127
00:08:15,037 --> 00:08:17,831
I've been busy since I left the syndicate.

128
00:08:18,332 --> 00:08:20,167
All right, come in.

129
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:36,183
So we're finally doing this?

130
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:39,519
After hiding like a coward.

131
00:08:39,603 --> 00:08:41,271
We're doing this.

132
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:44,066
Let's meet at the old café in Baltazar.

133
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,609
No funny business.

134
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:48,028
Don't try to call the police.

135
00:08:48,654 --> 00:08:51,490
Otherwise, you'll be getting back
your sister's corpse.

136
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:19,851
Be alert.

137
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,687
Let's go.

138
00:10:11,987 --> 00:10:13,488
Where's Teo?

139
00:10:14,364 --> 00:10:16,950
We're the ones you need. So here we are.

140
00:10:17,576 --> 00:10:19,077
Are you kidding me?

141
00:10:19,995 --> 00:10:21,997
Teo's supposed to be here.
That's the deal.

142
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,790
Papa, please.

143
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:25,667
Let's end this.

144
00:10:25,751 --> 00:10:28,420
Give Issay back so we can have peace!

145
00:10:28,503 --> 00:10:29,921
Peace?

146
00:10:30,714 --> 00:10:31,631
We had that

147
00:10:31,715 --> 00:10:35,469
before Gem and that shameless Teo
came along.

148
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:38,055
And you.

149
00:10:39,014 --> 00:10:41,641
Don't you ever think
that we accepted you again

150
00:10:41,725 --> 00:10:43,226
because you matter.

151
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,396
We only want Ace's child.

152
00:10:47,856 --> 00:10:48,857
I know.

153
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,651
I expect nothing from you people.

154
00:10:53,362 --> 00:10:55,989
Let's get to the point. Where is Issay?

155
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:02,245
Inside the car.

156
00:11:03,246 --> 00:11:05,582
We'll let her out
once you come with us.

157
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,794
We're not going anywhere
until I see Issay!

158
00:11:09,336 --> 00:11:11,254
Stop messing with me.

159
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:13,215
I know a trap when I see one.

160
00:11:14,466 --> 00:11:16,343
Gem!

161
00:11:16,426 --> 00:11:19,096
- Pa!
- Is this what you want?

162
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:20,639
Gem, what are you doing?

163
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:21,973
I'll kill her.

164
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:24,267
You can't do that.

165
00:11:24,351 --> 00:11:26,853
Pa... Gem.

166
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:31,525
I've done far worse things
than you know, Judge Divino!

167
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:34,903
Pa!

168
00:11:37,197 --> 00:11:38,782
Don't hurt my daughter.

169
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:41,618
- Bring Issay out here!
- Pa!

170
00:11:57,634 --> 00:11:58,844
Take one more step,

171
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:01,346
and I'll blow her brains out!

172
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:04,057
Papa. Papa, please.

173
00:12:04,141 --> 00:12:05,934
Be quiet.

174
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:08,812
Did you really think I cared about you?

175
00:12:08,895 --> 00:12:10,522
Gem...

176
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:13,525
I'm losing my patience.

177
00:12:14,317 --> 00:12:16,278
See?

178
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,905
Now, hand over Issay!

179
00:12:18,989 --> 00:12:21,616
Papa!

180
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:43,972
- Issay! Are you okay?
- Teo.

181
00:12:44,055 --> 00:12:45,223
Come on. Get up.

182
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:49,603
Raya.

183
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:51,563
Papa!

184
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,607
- Move!
- Raya.

185
00:12:58,862 --> 00:13:01,364
Pa! Papa!

186
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:13,043
Go after them!

187
00:13:21,176 --> 00:13:22,594
Get in!

188
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:26,139
- Let's go, Teo!
- You guys go already.

189
00:13:26,223 --> 00:13:27,390
- I'm going back for them!
- What?

190
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:28,850
- Go!
- Papa.

191
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:39,486
Go!

192
00:13:43,907 --> 00:13:45,075
Get in!

193
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:52,832
Let's go!

194
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:22,487
What happened, Divino?

195
00:14:23,238 --> 00:14:24,823
They got Issay.

196
00:14:24,906 --> 00:14:27,784
- What? And Raya?
- What about Gem?

197
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:29,619
It was all a sham.

198
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:32,247
Gem held Raya hostage
so they could escape.

199
00:14:32,330 --> 00:14:35,834
Oh, no! So Raya's still with them?

200
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:37,419
My child.

201
00:14:37,502 --> 00:14:39,254
I will get my child.

202
00:14:39,337 --> 00:14:41,631
Ace, Ace. Take it easy.

203
00:14:41,715 --> 00:14:44,092
Your wounds are still healing.

204
00:14:44,175 --> 00:14:45,343
Now what?

205
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:47,721
Teo's sister is gone.

206
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:49,180
We have no leverage.

207
00:14:49,264 --> 00:14:53,018
Leverage is only useful
if we're negotiating.

208
00:14:53,101 --> 00:14:54,978
And I'm done negotiating!

209
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,522
This isn't over.

210
00:15:04,821 --> 00:15:07,657
Eat up, sweetie.

211
00:15:08,575 --> 00:15:10,160
You've lost so much weight.

212
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:11,870
Weren't they feeding you?

213
00:15:11,953 --> 00:15:15,081
They gave me food, but I wouldn't eat it.

214
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:20,170
What's the matter, Issay?

215
00:15:21,671 --> 00:15:23,590
I love you so much, Ma.

216
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:28,845
You're safe now.

217
00:15:29,471 --> 00:15:32,098
We will never lose you again.

218
00:15:32,182 --> 00:15:34,100
This family is staying together.

219
00:15:36,478 --> 00:15:38,563
You're not leaving, are you, Mama?

220
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:42,525
Don't worry, I'm not going anywhere.

221
00:15:43,318 --> 00:15:44,819
Eat your food, sweetie.

222
00:15:44,903 --> 00:15:46,154
Go ahead.

223
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:50,742
Are you okay?

224
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:55,789
That was the first time
I saw my father that violent.

225
00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:01,378
I saw a monster, not a man.

226
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:03,213
He shot at us.

227
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,676
We're in the middle of this mess, Raya.

228
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:08,968
It can't be avoided.

229
00:16:09,052 --> 00:16:11,429
Maybe he sees me as an enemy now.

230
00:16:11,513 --> 00:16:13,848
But I still have to fix what I've done.

231
00:16:13,932 --> 00:16:15,225
Can you help me?

232
00:16:15,684 --> 00:16:16,768
How?

233
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,187
My name is Raya Verona.

234
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:23,316
I want to make it clear to everyone
that I was not kidnapped.

235
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:28,822
I willingly came
with Ronnie Manalang and his group.

236
00:16:28,905 --> 00:16:32,200
No one forced me,
no one threatened me.

237
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:35,036
It was my decision to leave home,

238
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,622
to get away from my family.

239
00:16:37,706 --> 00:16:40,208
The people I'm with are not criminals.

240
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:43,670
I am not missing,
and I have not been kidnapped.

241
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:46,047
This is my choice.

242
00:16:46,131 --> 00:16:48,675
Mateo Crisanto,

243
00:16:48,758 --> 00:16:50,760
<i>Alonzo Crisanto,</i>

244
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:52,512
<i>Rita Crisanto,</i>

245
00:16:52,595 --> 00:16:53,847
<i>and Gem Verona are innocent.</i>

246
00:16:56,891 --> 00:16:59,853
We gave her everything.

247
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:01,020
Everything!

248
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:04,315
That ungrateful brat!

249
00:17:04,941 --> 00:17:07,110
Let her stay there and suffer!

250
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:08,945
She is no longer a Verona.

251
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,322
But she is a Verona, Ace.

252
00:17:11,406 --> 00:17:13,408
That's why she's the way she is.

253
00:17:13,491 --> 00:17:15,076
Impulsive.

254
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,369
Bullheaded.

255
00:17:16,453 --> 00:17:17,912
Persistent.

256
00:17:17,996 --> 00:17:22,792
So no matter what she says in that video,
your sister needs to come back to us.

257
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:24,627
But make no mistake...

258
00:17:26,296 --> 00:17:28,548
she will crawl back.

259
00:17:28,631 --> 00:17:30,633
And when she comes home,

260
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:35,346
she will face
the full weight of her choices.

261
00:17:45,106 --> 00:17:47,025
Pa, I was thinking,

262
00:17:47,776 --> 00:17:51,362
before we escape, we should
at least weaken the Veronas.

263
00:17:51,446 --> 00:17:52,655
If we weaken them,

264
00:17:52,739 --> 00:17:55,158
they can't find us or stop us,

265
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:57,577
no matter where we go.

266
00:18:34,697 --> 00:18:35,782
Steven.

267
00:18:38,576 --> 00:18:39,661
What are you doing here?

268
00:18:41,037 --> 00:18:42,872
What are you hiding there?

269
00:18:44,374 --> 00:18:45,792
Does your boss know?

270
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:48,127
Mind your own business.

271
00:18:48,211 --> 00:18:50,547
We all do what we must do to get by.

272
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:53,049
So you're proud of what you're doing?

273
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:57,387
What if you end up
inside one of those cars next?

274
00:18:57,470 --> 00:19:00,765
You know
how the Veronas deal with traitors.

275
00:19:00,849 --> 00:19:02,600
Say goodbye to your pension...

276
00:19:02,684 --> 00:19:04,435
...and hello to a grave.

277
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:11,860
Teo, don't rat me out.

278
00:19:11,943 --> 00:19:14,362
I won't send this to Divino

279
00:19:14,445 --> 00:19:18,199
if you tell me
where the cars are being shipped next.

280
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:23,162
All right, I'll tell you.

281
00:19:23,246 --> 00:19:24,747
In full detail.

282
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:27,667
- Where?
- Pier 13.

283
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,127
There are three luxury cars.

284
00:19:29,711 --> 00:19:31,129
Crate number 27.

285
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:04,162
I'll take the video.
I'll record everything.

286
00:20:04,245 --> 00:20:06,956
- The crates, the transfers, all of it.
- Okay.

287
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,877
Wait. Why aren't Hans
and the cops here yet?

288
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:14,881
We can't wait for them anymore.

289
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:16,299
- Huh?
- Leave it to me.

290
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:17,842
I'll distract the guards.

291
00:20:18,343 --> 00:20:20,428
- Okay.
- Let's go.

292
00:20:20,511 --> 00:20:21,679
Be careful.

293
00:20:27,977 --> 00:20:29,562
All right. You can go now.

294
00:20:30,021 --> 00:20:32,774
They're headed this way. Go, go!

295
00:22:24,093 --> 00:22:26,512
Let's go. This way.

296
00:22:26,888 --> 00:22:28,056
- Hey!
- Go!

297
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,185
Hurry. Come on.

298
00:23:24,487 --> 00:23:26,614
This way. Come on, hurry.

299
00:23:26,697 --> 00:23:30,159
Here we can see
the smuggled cars of the Veronas.

300
00:23:30,243 --> 00:23:31,494
- There are diamonds inside.
- Sir.

301
00:23:31,577 --> 00:23:34,580
- There are more here.
- Come on.

302
00:23:34,664 --> 00:23:36,749
- This way.
- Take a video.

303
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:39,293
Make sure to get everything,
including that side.

304
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:42,505
We received a tip about the shipment.

305
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:44,632
There is probable cause
for a warrant to be issued.

306
00:23:44,715 --> 00:23:48,803
You dragged our family into this mess
just because of a tip?

307
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:50,847
How dare you!

308
00:23:51,389 --> 00:23:53,641
Who was the judge who issued the warrant?

309
00:23:54,809 --> 00:23:57,562
I hope the affidavit was sufficient

310
00:23:57,645 --> 00:24:01,732
because if it wasn't,
then everything you seized

311
00:24:01,816 --> 00:24:04,652
becomes fruit of the poisonous tree.

312
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:06,529
Illegal search.

313
00:24:06,612 --> 00:24:08,573
Tainted evidence.

314
00:24:08,656 --> 00:24:10,741
Inadmissible.

315
00:24:10,825 --> 00:24:13,327
And all of this will go down in court...

316
00:24:13,411 --> 00:24:15,163
...spectacularly.

317
00:24:15,246 --> 00:24:18,708
Yes. But the chain of circumstances
says otherwise.

318
00:24:18,791 --> 00:24:20,668
Both the shipment
and Mr. Verona's vintage cars

319
00:24:20,751 --> 00:24:22,086
have the same exporter.

320
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:23,880
The time of delivery also matched.

321
00:24:23,963 --> 00:24:25,798
We also got testimonies
from the people at the pier.

322
00:24:25,882 --> 00:24:27,508
And according to them,

323
00:24:27,592 --> 00:24:30,720
it was your staff
who usually handled the shipment.

324
00:24:30,803 --> 00:24:33,097
You didn't catch us holding a diamond.

325
00:24:33,181 --> 00:24:35,183
There is no actual possession.

326
00:24:35,266 --> 00:24:37,393
There is no contractual possession.

327
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:40,229
There is <i>no flagrante delicto.</i>

328
00:24:41,314 --> 00:24:45,151
So no.
You have no grounds to arrest us.

329
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:48,487
The prosecutor will conduct
a preliminary investigation.

330
00:24:48,571 --> 00:24:49,572
Good.

331
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:53,492
I look forward
to cross-examining your evidence.

332
00:24:53,576 --> 00:24:56,662
And if your warrant is proven to be wrong,

333
00:24:56,746 --> 00:25:00,374
I will sue you for abuse of authority,

334
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:04,378
malicious prosecution,
administrative liability.

335
00:25:04,921 --> 00:25:06,756
And if I were you,

336
00:25:06,839 --> 00:25:11,052
I would start documenting everything
very carefully.

337
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:14,013
Katarina, let's go.

338
00:25:16,766 --> 00:25:18,434
We will be there.

339
00:25:27,818 --> 00:25:31,405
The smuggled gemstones
are now in the custody of the police.

340
00:25:31,489 --> 00:25:34,784
Hans is keeping an eye on them, too.
That will restrict their movements.

341
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:39,247
Next, we'll take down
their human trafficking operations.

342
00:25:41,290 --> 00:25:42,333
Ma.

343
00:25:42,917 --> 00:25:45,586
I don't have access
to their operations anymore.

344
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:48,130
But I'll try.

345
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:56,681
- <i>Boss.</i>
- Hello, Adela?

346
00:25:56,764 --> 00:25:57,932
Do you have an update?

347
00:25:58,015 --> 00:26:00,351
Yes, Boss. I talked to our contacts.

348
00:26:00,851 --> 00:26:04,021
<i>Attorney Alberto is in charge</i>
<i>of the operations.</i>

349
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,982
<i>There will be another shipment.</i>

350
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:07,608
<i>There are 15 of them.</i>

351
00:26:12,363 --> 00:26:15,366
Attorney Alberto?
The ex-legal attaché in Morocco?

352
00:26:15,449 --> 00:26:18,494
Yes. He was the one
who helped get you out of jail.

353
00:26:18,577 --> 00:26:21,539
They changed all the operation plans

354
00:26:21,622 --> 00:26:23,708
because I was the one who organized it.

355
00:26:23,791 --> 00:26:27,086
I tracked it,
but Divino has my laptop now.

356
00:26:27,169 --> 00:26:28,796
All the files we need are saved there.

357
00:26:28,879 --> 00:26:30,381
We need to get it immediately.

358
00:26:30,464 --> 00:26:33,217
They won't be able
to open the laptop easily...

359
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:36,345
...but it contains
all the evidence

360
00:26:36,429 --> 00:26:39,098
of their human smuggling operations.

361
00:26:39,181 --> 00:26:41,892
I'll break into the law office
of Divino and Ace.

362
00:26:41,976 --> 00:26:46,439
The app says that my laptop
is at the Veronas' house.

363
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:48,941
Their house is huge, Ma.
Where exactly is it?

364
00:26:49,025 --> 00:26:51,110
The app can't pinpoint the exact location,

365
00:26:51,193 --> 00:26:54,780
but if the phone is at a closer range
to the laptop we're looking for,

366
00:26:54,864 --> 00:26:57,241
it will give us direction to where it is.

367
00:26:57,742 --> 00:26:59,660
It's probably at their home office.

368
00:26:59,744 --> 00:27:02,747
That's where they keep important files.

369
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:05,875
And fortunately, it has no CCTV cameras
because Ace didn't want them.

370
00:27:05,958 --> 00:27:07,960
We got Issay already.

371
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:10,838
We have our escape plan ready.

372
00:27:11,714 --> 00:27:14,050
Why do we have to do this?

373
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:15,468
For justice.

374
00:27:15,551 --> 00:27:17,845
Justice for their victims,

375
00:27:17,928 --> 00:27:20,097
and to stop them
from claiming more victims.

376
00:27:20,181 --> 00:27:22,850
We have to take them down
and send them to jail.

377
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:26,604
And so that no one will come after us
and threaten us.

378
00:27:27,229 --> 00:27:28,898
So we can live a quiet life.

379
00:27:37,365 --> 00:27:39,241
You're so kind to me, Ronnie.

380
00:27:39,325 --> 00:27:41,660
Even though we're in this situation...

381
00:27:43,621 --> 00:27:45,623
I'm so lucky that we're together.

382
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:47,792
Me too.

383
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:50,586
But I've made up my mind.

384
00:27:52,546 --> 00:27:54,548
I'm going back home.

385
00:27:55,132 --> 00:27:56,133
What?

386
00:27:57,134 --> 00:27:59,428
I can't lie to you, Ronnie.

387
00:27:59,512 --> 00:28:01,597
We've been through a lot together.

388
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:04,100
I know about Teo's plan.

389
00:28:04,183 --> 00:28:06,894
He'll get the laptop
so he can have evidence

390
00:28:06,977 --> 00:28:09,563
to take down my family.

391
00:28:11,148 --> 00:28:12,817
They'll go to jail, Ronnie.

392
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:16,195
- If only I could stop them--
- No, you shouldn't.

393
00:28:18,114 --> 00:28:19,782
Teo's right.

394
00:28:21,951 --> 00:28:24,453
But I can't let my family go to jail.

395
00:28:25,037 --> 00:28:28,290
I have to go home and destroy that laptop.

396
00:28:30,251 --> 00:28:32,586
- Or else--
- Or else what?

397
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:34,839
Doing that is obstruction of justice.

398
00:28:36,674 --> 00:28:38,926
Did you know that my family
was a victim of your agency?

399
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:42,138
Raya, I became an orphan
because of your family.

400
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:45,057
That's why I want justice.

401
00:28:46,475 --> 00:28:48,978
Nothing can change my mind, Ronnie.

402
00:28:50,438 --> 00:28:54,108
I can't bear to see
my family in jail. I have to do something.

403
00:28:54,650 --> 00:28:56,735
I wish you hadn't told me this.

404
00:28:56,819 --> 00:28:59,405
It's hard to decide who I should protect.

405
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:03,576
Should I choose you
or the family that I have now?

406
00:29:06,370 --> 00:29:07,705
I know.

407
00:29:07,788 --> 00:29:09,206
I'm sorry.

408
00:29:15,004 --> 00:29:17,339
But you don't have to take my side.

409
00:29:18,841 --> 00:29:21,927
I just don't want to leave
without saying goodbye to you.

410
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:27,641
Goodbye, Ronnie.

411
00:29:42,948 --> 00:29:47,620
"Teo, Raya is going back to her family."

412
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,802
Divino,
you better be thinking

413
00:30:03,886 --> 00:30:06,430
of how to skin Teo and Gem alive.

414
00:30:06,514 --> 00:30:08,390
Or else...

415
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:15,147
Eric.

416
00:30:15,231 --> 00:30:16,982
<i>Hello, Judge. Good evening.</i>

417
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:21,070
Are you familiar
with the name or surname Kassir?

418
00:30:21,153 --> 00:30:25,241
Yes, that was the surname
Gem used in Morocco. Why?

419
00:30:25,324 --> 00:30:27,159
I got a report that someone

420
00:30:27,243 --> 00:30:29,787
saw Teo and Ma'am Gem
at a small columbarium.

421
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:31,080
Columbarium?

422
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:32,873
Who the hell died?

423
00:30:32,957 --> 00:30:34,458
<i>According to the filed report,</i>

424
00:30:34,542 --> 00:30:38,420
it was Yanadia Kassir, Judge.

425
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:39,838
It was a baby.

426
00:30:43,384 --> 00:30:44,718
Did Gem die?

427
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:47,513
No.

428
00:30:47,596 --> 00:30:49,014
Gem did not die.

429
00:30:50,266 --> 00:30:51,892
The baby did.

430
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:57,022
Take it easy. Be careful.

431
00:30:57,106 --> 00:30:58,190
Okay.

432
00:30:58,983 --> 00:31:01,569
We're good.

433
00:31:04,113 --> 00:31:06,865
Larajean. You know the drill.

434
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:15,749
Ace...

435
00:31:15,833 --> 00:31:17,626
There's something you should know.

436
00:31:17,710 --> 00:31:19,128
Um...

437
00:31:19,753 --> 00:31:21,422
And this news is...

438
00:31:22,381 --> 00:31:23,924
quite shocking.

439
00:31:24,008 --> 00:31:25,342
Why?

440
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:28,846
Is it about Gem?
Did something happen to her?

441
00:31:28,929 --> 00:31:32,474
Gem and Teo went to a columbarium
to put someone to rest.

442
00:31:33,851 --> 00:31:34,852
Who?

443
00:31:38,147 --> 00:31:39,648
Don't tell me...

444
00:31:42,401 --> 00:31:43,652
No!

445
00:31:43,736 --> 00:31:45,988
We double-checked
with the columbarium.

446
00:31:47,031 --> 00:31:48,616
We're sorry, Ace.

447
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:51,577
The baby died.

448
00:31:55,789 --> 00:31:57,207
I'm gonna kill that woman!

449
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:00,878
Bring me Gem right now!

450
00:32:00,961 --> 00:32:02,296
I'll kill that woman!

451
00:32:02,379 --> 00:32:03,589
I will kill Gem!

452
00:32:03,672 --> 00:32:05,215
- I'm gonna kill her!
- Ace, Ace.

453
00:32:05,299 --> 00:32:07,384
- She can't do that to me and my baby!
- No, no, no, no, no!

454
00:32:07,468 --> 00:32:10,137
Ace, Ace! Ace, please control yourself!

455
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:12,640
- Control yourself. Calm down.
- How could she do this?

456
00:32:12,723 --> 00:32:14,642
Calm down. Calm down.

457
00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:18,854
How could she do that?

458
00:32:46,298 --> 00:32:48,801
Where the hell did you come from?

459
00:32:48,884 --> 00:32:50,177
Whose car was that?

460
00:33:02,398 --> 00:33:03,941
Park it over there.

461
00:33:23,544 --> 00:33:26,380
No one should know that Raya is back.

462
00:33:26,922 --> 00:33:28,424
Okay. Thank you.

463
00:33:29,633 --> 00:33:31,844
I'm really sorry for everything.

464
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:34,221
Well, you should be sorry, Raya.

465
00:33:34,304 --> 00:33:35,514
What matters is that

466
00:33:35,597 --> 00:33:37,474
you left those good-for-nothing people

467
00:33:37,558 --> 00:33:39,143
and you're here.

468
00:33:39,226 --> 00:33:41,186
You're back as you should.

469
00:33:41,270 --> 00:33:42,604
Where are they?

470
00:33:43,897 --> 00:33:44,982
Um...

471
00:33:46,442 --> 00:33:48,694
Uh... we were...

472
00:33:50,738 --> 00:33:53,657
we were changing location a lot, Papa.

473
00:33:53,741 --> 00:33:55,576
It's so hard to keep track.

474
00:33:56,994 --> 00:33:59,913
We were headed north when I escaped.

475
00:33:59,997 --> 00:34:01,248
Somewhere...

476
00:34:01,749 --> 00:34:03,167
Somewhere in Masantol.

477
00:34:04,626 --> 00:34:06,837
I don't know where they are now.

478
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:09,173
They took my phone,
so I didn't have access to the Internet.

479
00:34:09,256 --> 00:34:10,466
Damn it, Raya!

480
00:34:11,967 --> 00:34:13,260
You've been with them for a long time.

481
00:34:13,343 --> 00:34:16,138
How can I believe
you don't know where they live?

482
00:34:16,221 --> 00:34:18,098
For all I know, they have brainwashed you.

483
00:34:18,182 --> 00:34:19,349
No!

484
00:34:20,225 --> 00:34:23,061
Pa, I came back because I missed you.

485
00:34:24,271 --> 00:34:26,482
And I regret going with Ronnie.

486
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:30,027
I didn't know
he was with Teo and everyone else.

487
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:31,487
But you're one of them.

488
00:34:31,904 --> 00:34:35,324
Remember how they got Issay, Teo's sister?

489
00:34:35,407 --> 00:34:36,658
Divino.

490
00:34:37,493 --> 00:34:39,912
I was afraid that you'd hurt me, too.

491
00:34:41,789 --> 00:34:43,373
You were so mad at me.

492
00:34:44,666 --> 00:34:45,834
And maybe...

493
00:34:46,543 --> 00:34:48,545
maybe I'm brainwashed or something.

494
00:34:48,629 --> 00:34:50,547
I don't know.

495
00:34:50,631 --> 00:34:51,924
But I snapped when I heard

496
00:34:52,007 --> 00:34:54,426
about Uncle Jorge
being dumped in a dumpsite.

497
00:34:57,471 --> 00:34:59,431
Plus, the news about our family.

498
00:34:59,515 --> 00:35:02,893
I just...
I just wanted to leave!

499
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:05,687
I wasn't planning on meeting with Teo.

500
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:09,149
But because of all the chaos that night,

501
00:35:09,650 --> 00:35:11,318
I went with them.

502
00:35:11,401 --> 00:35:12,653
But Raya...

503
00:35:13,237 --> 00:35:14,988
Raya, that was so stupid.

504
00:35:15,072 --> 00:35:16,573
I know, Ma.

505
00:35:16,657 --> 00:35:18,116
And I am sorry.

506
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,369
I'm really sorry.

507
00:35:21,453 --> 00:35:22,371
Pa!

508
00:35:22,830 --> 00:35:24,456
Please believe me.

509
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:27,125
I just want to be with you.

510
00:35:27,209 --> 00:35:29,002
I'm tired.

511
00:35:29,086 --> 00:35:31,588
I'm really... I am tired.

512
00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:15,173
Raya is lying.

513
00:36:17,301 --> 00:36:20,053
Well, I don't have any reason
to believe she's not.

514
00:36:21,221 --> 00:36:23,140
But I'll get the truth out of her.

515
00:36:23,223 --> 00:36:24,641
Don't worry about it.

516
00:36:25,684 --> 00:36:28,020
While you're at it,
don't let her out of your sight.

517
00:36:28,103 --> 00:36:30,355
I went over the figures earlier.

518
00:36:31,523 --> 00:36:36,361
And it looks like
we're losing one billion pesos

519
00:36:36,445 --> 00:36:39,615
because of the jewelry
the authorities confiscated.

520
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,534
We still have a lot left, right?

521
00:36:42,618 --> 00:36:44,036
There's plenty left.

522
00:36:44,119 --> 00:36:46,914
Our income from human trafficking
is separate.

523
00:36:46,997 --> 00:36:49,875
And they're all
in an online offshore account.

524
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,418
So, good.

525
00:36:51,501 --> 00:36:54,463
All you need to do
is to access those accounts, right?

526
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:56,381
I believe they're all in your name.

527
00:36:56,465 --> 00:36:57,507
Of course not.

528
00:36:57,591 --> 00:36:59,009
Nobody does that.

529
00:36:59,092 --> 00:37:02,429
If the authorities poke around,
that's strong evidence against me.

530
00:37:02,512 --> 00:37:04,097
Wait, wait, wait.

531
00:37:04,973 --> 00:37:06,224
No.

532
00:37:06,308 --> 00:37:09,645
I mean... how could you?

533
00:37:09,728 --> 00:37:13,398
Divino,
whose name is all that money under?

534
00:37:14,775 --> 00:37:16,777
She was a business partner.

535
00:37:17,277 --> 00:37:18,946
She handled everything from that end.

536
00:37:19,029 --> 00:37:21,573
No!

537
00:37:22,574 --> 00:37:25,994
I knew it was Pearl!
Who else could it be?

538
00:37:27,204 --> 00:37:28,956
How could you have done that?

539
00:37:29,039 --> 00:37:31,333
That's so foolish, Divino!

540
00:37:31,416 --> 00:37:35,128
You mean to say
you registered all those funds

541
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:37,047
under your mistress's name?

542
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:39,800
You better get those out now!

543
00:37:39,883 --> 00:37:42,094
Move the money online
before it's too late!

544
00:37:44,388 --> 00:37:46,556
Pearl has the password
and access to the account.

545
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:49,851
My God,
it even makes it worse!

546
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:55,524
Divino, how much money
are we talking about here?

547
00:37:56,858 --> 00:37:58,276
120 billion.

548
00:37:58,360 --> 00:38:00,696
Oh, my goodness!

549
00:38:02,990 --> 00:38:06,660
I already contacted
a tech expert from Singapore.

550
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:08,912
I have Pearl's laptop.

551
00:38:08,996 --> 00:38:10,330
We can start from there.

552
00:38:10,414 --> 00:38:12,332
What about her access to operations?

553
00:38:12,416 --> 00:38:14,626
She has no access to our operations.

554
00:38:14,710 --> 00:38:16,753
Well, good thing you thought of that.

555
00:38:16,837 --> 00:38:20,424
But Divino, that money,
you better get that out!

556
00:38:21,717 --> 00:38:23,802
It cannot be lost!

557
00:38:23,885 --> 00:38:25,012
It won't.

558
00:38:27,347 --> 00:38:29,850
That 120 billion is mine.

559
00:38:30,851 --> 00:38:32,185
Ours.

560
00:38:33,103 --> 00:38:36,523
No one else gets to profit
from my hard work.

561
00:38:37,441 --> 00:38:39,109
I'll make sure of that.

562
00:39:28,075 --> 00:39:29,743
<i>What could the password be?</i>

563
00:39:29,826 --> 00:39:31,244
<i>Maybe Papa's birthday?</i>

564
00:39:34,706 --> 00:39:36,041
<i>My birthday?</i>

565
00:39:36,124 --> 00:39:38,418
<i>April 27th, 2005.</i>

566
00:39:40,170 --> 00:39:41,588
<i>- Check!</i>

567
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:02,651
- Over here.
- Inside.

568
00:40:03,401 --> 00:40:04,903
- Come on.
- Okay.

569
00:40:07,656 --> 00:40:08,740
Let's go.

570
00:40:14,287 --> 00:40:15,205
Where?

571
00:40:16,373 --> 00:40:17,541
Raya here.

572
00:40:20,377 --> 00:40:21,378
Good.

573
00:40:21,461 --> 00:40:23,296
You still remember me.

574
00:40:25,298 --> 00:40:26,967
Because I remember...

575
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:29,302
you were the tech genius
of our class back then.

576
00:40:29,386 --> 00:40:30,720
Can you help me?

577
00:40:32,097 --> 00:40:34,432
Retina access key.

578
00:40:37,102 --> 00:40:38,145
It'll be hard?

579
00:40:38,228 --> 00:40:40,272
Oh, come on, Mel. You can do it.

580
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:01,084
I need to open this

581
00:41:01,168 --> 00:41:05,005
only to have all of its files destroyed.

582
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,008
Possible?

583
00:41:09,050 --> 00:41:10,427
Yay!

584
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:11,803
Okay.

585
00:41:11,887 --> 00:41:13,805
I'll bring it to you tomorrow.

586
00:41:14,764 --> 00:41:17,184
Thank you, Mel. Bye.

587
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:27,861
Come on.

588
00:41:45,295 --> 00:41:46,630
Which way?

589
00:41:47,881 --> 00:41:48,882
What does it say?

590
00:41:50,383 --> 00:41:51,801
That's Raya's room.

591
00:42:24,584 --> 00:42:26,586
- Where?
- Here.

592
00:42:57,325 --> 00:42:59,244
Why? What happened?

593
00:42:59,327 --> 00:43:03,373
Divino blocked me
from the Human Smuggling Operations.

594
00:43:03,456 --> 00:43:05,333
What are we going to do?
We're out of time.

595
00:43:05,417 --> 00:43:07,752
I still have the password
to the offshore accounts.

596
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:09,170
Try it.

597
00:43:19,347 --> 00:43:20,432
Hard drive.

598
00:43:51,963 --> 00:43:55,800
Put that down,
or I'll scream.

599
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:03,892
You think I'm joking?

600
00:44:04,476 --> 00:44:06,895
One scream,
one call to the police...

601
00:44:07,395 --> 00:44:08,730
...and you're both out.

602
00:44:08,813 --> 00:44:10,523
My parents hate you guys so much,

603
00:44:10,607 --> 00:44:13,068
you'll both rot in prison for sure.

604
00:44:13,151 --> 00:44:15,195
- Raya, listen to us.
- No!

605
00:44:15,278 --> 00:44:16,529
You listen to me.

606
00:44:24,496 --> 00:44:25,413
Open it.

607
00:44:25,497 --> 00:44:27,332
What do you need the laptop for?

608
00:44:27,415 --> 00:44:31,086
In any case, you're not even
part of your father's operations.

609
00:44:31,169 --> 00:44:33,004
Just open it.

610
00:44:33,421 --> 00:44:34,672
I'm not stupid.

611
00:44:35,465 --> 00:44:36,633
I know your plans.

612
00:44:36,716 --> 00:44:39,010
You're not going to use
what's inside that as evidence.

613
00:44:48,019 --> 00:44:51,106
That laptop must never be recovered.

614
00:44:51,523 --> 00:44:53,441
Every file, info,

615
00:44:53,942 --> 00:44:56,111
and details that put my parents...

616
00:44:56,194 --> 00:44:58,613
my father to jail.

617
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:01,408
Delete everything.

618
00:45:02,534 --> 00:45:04,285
Before she deletes everything,

619
00:45:04,369 --> 00:45:07,789
we need to make sure
we get out of here without them knowing.

620
00:45:07,872 --> 00:45:11,084
If we give you
what you want for your family,

621
00:45:11,626 --> 00:45:13,211
give us what we want too.

622
00:45:13,837 --> 00:45:16,423
We also have families
we're trying to protect.

623
00:45:16,881 --> 00:45:18,049
Fine.

624
00:45:19,426 --> 00:45:22,512
This is for Ronnie
and the people he loves.

625
00:45:25,682 --> 00:45:26,850
Delete it.

626
00:45:44,826 --> 00:45:46,411
There, check it.

627
00:45:46,870 --> 00:45:48,037
It's gone.

628
00:46:13,813 --> 00:46:15,231
You can leave now.

629
00:46:15,315 --> 00:46:17,066
You know your way around, Teo.

630
00:46:20,236 --> 00:46:21,404
Let's go.

631
00:46:47,514 --> 00:46:48,348
Teo?

632
00:46:49,474 --> 00:46:51,643
Teo, what are you doing here?

633
00:46:54,437 --> 00:46:56,272
- Guards!
- Larajean!

634
00:46:56,356 --> 00:46:58,274
- Guards!
- Larajean, no!

635
00:46:58,358 --> 00:47:00,151
- Guards!
- Ma, let's run!

636
00:47:00,235 --> 00:47:01,945
- Guards, there they are!
- Hurry!

637
00:47:02,028 --> 00:47:03,696
- Chase them, hurry!
- Hey!

638
00:47:09,494 --> 00:47:11,162
What was that?

639
00:47:15,166 --> 00:47:16,918
What was that, Divino?

640
00:47:18,336 --> 00:47:20,255
Divino!

641
00:47:20,338 --> 00:47:21,839
The question is who.

642
00:47:21,923 --> 00:47:22,924
What?

643
00:47:23,007 --> 00:47:25,176
Teo and Pearl are here.

644
00:47:25,677 --> 00:47:27,929
They definitely fell for my trap.

645
00:47:52,161 --> 00:47:53,162
Ma, let's go!

646
00:48:12,932 --> 00:48:16,769
Dad, I was shocked they were inside,
and I stopped them!

647
00:48:17,478 --> 00:48:18,479
When I was with them,

648
00:48:18,563 --> 00:48:22,650
I heard Teo and Pearl talking about that
to destroy our family.

649
00:48:22,734 --> 00:48:25,361
So I destroyed the evidence for your sake!

650
00:48:25,445 --> 00:48:27,530
Now they have no proof.

651
00:48:27,614 --> 00:48:29,282
You won't go to jail.

652
00:48:29,365 --> 00:48:30,867
That was stupid!

653
00:48:31,242 --> 00:48:32,577
And foolish!

654
00:48:33,411 --> 00:48:36,414
All of our money is
in there, and Pearl has access!

655
00:48:36,914 --> 00:48:39,083
I know she's going to take
that laptop back

656
00:48:39,167 --> 00:48:41,127
from me, no matter what!

657
00:48:41,210 --> 00:48:43,963
Well, I don't really know
what's more foolish,

658
00:48:44,047 --> 00:48:45,298
what Raya did,

659
00:48:45,381 --> 00:48:48,426
or what you did
to entrust our entire future

660
00:48:48,509 --> 00:48:51,763
and put everything
in the name of that whore!

661
00:48:52,180 --> 00:48:55,683
I will get that retina access key
and open that blasted device.

662
00:48:55,767 --> 00:48:57,727
Even if I have to have her eyes taken out,

663
00:48:57,810 --> 00:48:59,520
I will get it open.

664
00:48:59,604 --> 00:49:01,773
Well, I really hope you do that, Divino.

665
00:49:02,315 --> 00:49:03,816
And you, Raya.

666
00:49:04,233 --> 00:49:06,819
If you don't know the full story,

667
00:49:06,903 --> 00:49:11,824
don't just jump in
and make your own decisions.

668
00:49:12,241 --> 00:49:15,244
We might lose all that money!

669
00:49:15,662 --> 00:49:16,663
Money!

670
00:49:16,746 --> 00:49:19,332
Always money! Money! Money!

671
00:49:20,208 --> 00:49:22,168
When will you ever be satisfied
with your wealth?

672
00:49:23,086 --> 00:49:26,589
Greed is consuming the both of you!

673
00:49:30,510 --> 00:49:32,929
You ungrateful brat!

674
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:36,391
Money rules.

675
00:49:37,684 --> 00:49:41,187
You know,
it's because you've been hanging around

676
00:49:41,270 --> 00:49:44,190
that poor Teo
that you've become like this.

677
00:49:44,273 --> 00:49:45,358
Ma'am.

678
00:49:46,442 --> 00:49:48,277
Ma'am, please stop.

679
00:49:48,361 --> 00:49:49,696
Shut up!

680
00:49:52,073 --> 00:49:54,075
You are going to the States...

681
00:49:54,158 --> 00:49:56,994
...so you can fix
that loser mindset of yours.

682
00:49:57,078 --> 00:49:59,831
Now go to your room
and think about what you did!

683
00:50:26,774 --> 00:50:28,609
Sir, I'm glad you made it.

684
00:50:28,693 --> 00:50:29,861
So here we go.

685
00:50:42,999 --> 00:50:44,917
Let's see what we got here.

686
00:50:46,294 --> 00:50:49,046
So... there you go.

687
00:50:50,506 --> 00:50:52,175
- Nice.
- Not bad.

688
00:50:52,258 --> 00:50:54,886
- Not bad at all. Yep.
- Not bad at all. We're in business.

689
00:51:23,873 --> 00:51:24,957
Hey!

690
00:51:57,698 --> 00:51:59,617
Let's go.
We need to get out of here.

691
00:51:59,992 --> 00:52:01,410
All of our papers were settled.

692
00:52:01,494 --> 00:52:03,037
We need to do this for our families.

693
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:05,748
We've already decided.
We're not backing out.

694
00:52:05,832 --> 00:52:09,752
The Veronas won't give you
the job they promised.

695
00:52:09,836 --> 00:52:11,879
They're going to sell you,
and you won't be able to go home.

696
00:52:11,963 --> 00:52:13,589
That's not what they told us.

697
00:52:13,673 --> 00:52:15,216
That's true.

698
00:52:15,299 --> 00:52:18,052
They'll sneak us in,
so we'll pay a lower placement fee.

699
00:52:18,135 --> 00:52:20,221
And then we'll get a nice job there.

700
00:52:20,304 --> 00:52:21,305
That's not true.

701
00:52:21,389 --> 00:52:24,141
When you get there,
a different job is waiting for you.

702
00:52:24,225 --> 00:52:25,268
Prostitution.

703
00:52:26,602 --> 00:52:29,230
You won't be sure
if you'll still return home alive.

704
00:52:29,313 --> 00:52:30,356
Come on, let's go.

705
00:52:31,566 --> 00:52:33,234
Let's hurry! The guards might arrive.

706
00:52:33,317 --> 00:52:35,611
- Hurry up!
- Let's go! Let's go!

707
00:52:35,695 --> 00:52:36,863
Shh! Keep it down.

708
00:52:41,242 --> 00:52:44,412
Sir, there's another container van
at the back. There are also people inside.

709
00:52:44,495 --> 00:52:46,831
Okay, I'll take care of it. Hurry.

710
00:52:54,797 --> 00:52:56,966
- Sir.
- What was that?

711
00:53:05,850 --> 00:53:07,435
Divino!

712
00:53:08,144 --> 00:53:09,312
Where's Divino?

713
00:53:09,395 --> 00:53:13,357
Had I known,
I would've let you rot in jail in Morocco!

714
00:53:13,441 --> 00:53:15,026
I'm innocent!

715
00:53:15,109 --> 00:53:16,986
You guys should be the ones
rotting in jail!

716
00:53:17,069 --> 00:53:18,321
Don't move.

717
00:53:28,497 --> 00:53:29,790
Don't move!

718
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:37,214
Attorney San Juan.

719
00:53:37,298 --> 00:53:38,341
Sir, what happened?

720
00:53:38,424 --> 00:53:39,842
I'm Colonel Robert Corpuz.

721
00:53:39,926 --> 00:53:42,219
And I know
you're not the only one running this.

722
00:53:42,303 --> 00:53:43,512
So tell me,

723
00:53:43,596 --> 00:53:45,723
who is the head of the whole operation?

724
00:53:45,806 --> 00:53:47,183
All of this,

725
00:53:47,266 --> 00:53:49,185
the system,

726
00:53:49,268 --> 00:53:52,438
the contacts at the dock
for those container vans,

727
00:53:52,521 --> 00:53:55,358
are all being managed by one person.

728
00:53:56,984 --> 00:53:58,778
It's Pearl Valdez.

729
00:53:58,861 --> 00:54:03,199
She's the head and leader
you've been looking for.

730
00:54:03,282 --> 00:54:05,034
Pearl Valdez.

731
00:54:06,410 --> 00:54:09,330
That's the alias of Rita Crisanto.

732
00:54:09,413 --> 00:54:12,625
Mateo Crisanto's mother.

733
00:54:17,713 --> 00:54:20,132
<i>Earlier today, authorities conducted</i>

734
00:54:20,216 --> 00:54:21,550
<i>a major operation against</i>

735
00:54:21,634 --> 00:54:24,971
<i>an international human smuggling network</i>

736
00:54:25,054 --> 00:54:27,223
<i>operating across several countries.</i>

737
00:54:27,306 --> 00:54:31,394
Based on documents and testimonies
now in our possession,

738
00:54:31,477 --> 00:54:35,314
the alleged head of this network
has been identified,

739
00:54:35,398 --> 00:54:37,817
after thorough investigation,

740
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:40,236
to be Rita Crisanto...

741
00:54:40,903 --> 00:54:44,323
also known as Pearl Valdez.

742
00:54:51,998 --> 00:54:54,500
I thought you guys were smart.

743
00:54:54,583 --> 00:54:58,713
Turns out Divino is smarter.

744
00:54:58,796 --> 00:55:01,007
He made you the mastermind, Ma.

745
00:55:03,217 --> 00:55:05,720
You know what, Rita? You should surrender.

746
00:55:06,178 --> 00:55:08,097
We might get dragged into this, too.

747
00:55:08,180 --> 00:55:09,390
Pa.

748
00:55:09,473 --> 00:55:11,726
Ma. Ma, please don't.

749
00:55:13,352 --> 00:55:18,107
We might not see each other again.
You might not be able to come back to us.

750
00:55:19,900 --> 00:55:21,318
Dear, it's all right.

751
00:55:21,986 --> 00:55:23,154
We're used to it anyway.

752
00:55:23,237 --> 00:55:26,490
Pa, no! I don't want to get used to it.

753
00:55:26,574 --> 00:55:28,909
I know it's okay for you
if she leaves, but I...

754
00:55:30,745 --> 00:55:33,581
I don't want her to, Pa.
I don't want her to.

755
00:55:34,790 --> 00:55:37,043
Ma, please don't.

756
00:55:46,677 --> 00:55:49,263
I am Divino Verona's right hand.

757
00:55:49,680 --> 00:55:53,100
I am the architect
of his human smuggling routes

758
00:55:54,060 --> 00:55:56,812
from Morocco across Southeast Asia.

759
00:55:56,896 --> 00:55:59,398
But when he found out that Teo is my son,

760
00:55:59,774 --> 00:56:01,358
he tried to have me killed.

761
00:56:07,573 --> 00:56:09,909
All of the transactions are in there.

762
00:56:10,242 --> 00:56:12,912
The lists of paid officials

763
00:56:13,913 --> 00:56:15,748
and international contacts.

764
00:56:16,415 --> 00:56:19,418
You know a lot about this. How?

765
00:56:28,469 --> 00:56:30,387
I was his mistress.

766
00:56:31,722 --> 00:56:33,641
In exchange for this,

767
00:56:34,266 --> 00:56:35,518
I want a deal.

768
00:56:36,143 --> 00:56:37,728
Total immunity.

769
00:56:37,812 --> 00:56:40,648
And you can't implicate me in any case.

770
00:56:40,981 --> 00:56:42,358
State witness.

771
00:56:45,277 --> 00:56:46,695
I will have it checked first.

772
00:56:50,699 --> 00:56:52,284
That's just a fraction of it.

773
00:56:52,368 --> 00:56:55,371
If you agree, I have more.

774
00:56:55,454 --> 00:56:58,582
But I think that information alone

775
00:56:58,666 --> 00:57:01,001
is already a huge help to you.

776
00:57:01,085 --> 00:57:03,003
What if you're just using the authorities

777
00:57:03,087 --> 00:57:04,421
to get rid of your enemies?

778
00:57:04,505 --> 00:57:06,048
You'd take over the operations instead.

779
00:57:06,465 --> 00:57:07,716
No.

780
00:57:10,177 --> 00:57:12,012
I just want to be a mother.

781
00:57:13,264 --> 00:57:14,932
A mother who can sleep peacefully

782
00:57:15,015 --> 00:57:17,518
with her children.

783
00:57:48,048 --> 00:57:50,801
- Ma...
- Raya...

784
00:57:54,054 --> 00:57:55,055
Attorney Lim.

785
00:57:55,639 --> 00:57:57,808
We're going to the police station now.

786
00:57:57,892 --> 00:57:59,685
I want a copy of the Complaint-Affidavit

787
00:57:59,768 --> 00:58:02,021
filed by Pearl Valdez
the moment we step in.

788
00:58:02,104 --> 00:58:03,022
Please make sure

789
00:58:03,105 --> 00:58:05,024
that our Counter-Affidavit outline
is ready.

790
00:58:05,107 --> 00:58:06,942
We are going to hit her credibility.

791
00:58:07,610 --> 00:58:09,486
See you at the station.

792
00:58:51,737 --> 00:58:54,907
You are
the architect of your own crimes.

793
00:58:54,990 --> 00:58:57,326
And you're just looking for a scapegoat.

794
00:58:57,409 --> 00:58:59,870
I was just following
your orders. It was all you!

795
00:58:59,954 --> 00:59:01,956
It's better for you to be alive
when I throw you into the river.

796
00:59:02,039 --> 00:59:04,792
- <i>So you will surely suffer.</i>
- Gem!

797
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:07,628
<i>In the end,</i>
<i>no matter what happens,</i>

798
00:59:07,711 --> 00:59:09,797
<i>love will never be gone.</i>

799
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:12,299
<i>I'm afraid that I'll lose you, too.</i>

800
00:59:12,383 --> 00:59:15,094
I can't let that wedding happen.

801
00:59:15,177 --> 00:59:16,262
<i>I'm all yours.</i>

802
00:59:16,345 --> 00:59:17,888
<i>Rest in hell.</i>
